The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
Archives
 The City Diary
																																																		Police have recovered a diary from the paternal home of Subhalakshmi Banerjee, 28, in which she has narrated how she was subjected to torture by her husband and in-laws within a few days of her marriage in January 2003. The police are trying to find out who the gents watch, found near Subhalakshmis body, belonged to. She was found dead at her paternal home in Shibpur on Thursday afternoon. Subhalakshmi was married to Sandip Banerjee, 32, a resident of Bandel, in Hooghly. She was in an advanced stage of pregnancy, and came to her paternal home a week ago. 																																																		Homemaker Madhu Thakur, 25, committed suicide by hanging herself in her bedroom at her Sabji Bagan Lane house on Friday. She has a two-and-a-half-year-old son.																																																		Preston Lewis Normal, 28, was killed after his motorcycle hit a Matador near Park Street on Friday. Pedestrian Yunus Ali Sardar, 55, was injured after being hit by a minibus in Ekbalpore.																																																		Extortionist Kamta Singh was arrested in Liluah on Friday. 
